    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-26T06:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-26T06:34:00-05:00" n="589"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d589">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1102: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-26T20:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 26, 1919, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received September 26, 6.39 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am positive Semenoff and Kalmarkoff<note n="35" xml:id="d589fn35">Undoubtedly
                        Kalmykov, Ataman of the Ussuri Cossacks.</note> intend to take possession
                    Chinese Eastern by force and with the many Japanese soldiers now on ground could
                    do so as improbable Chinese would fight. This action would be fatal blow to all
                    our good offices. There is some reason to believe that Chinese Government may be
                    asked to appoint Semenoff director of Chinese Eastern, [which] ought not to be
                    permitted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
